## Industry Learning Roadmap

If your goal is **AWS Cloud Engineer, DevOps Engineer, or System Administrator**, learn in this order:

1. Linux (Bash scripting)
2. Networking (IP, DNS, HTTP, HTTPS, SSH)
3. AWS IAM
4. EC2
5. VPC
6. S3
7. EBS & EFS
8. Load Balancer
9. Auto Scaling
10. RDS
11. CloudWatch
12. Route 53
13. CloudFront
14. Lambda
15. Infrastructure as Code (Terraform or AWS CloudFormation)
16. Docker
17. Kubernetes
18. CI/CD (Jenkins or GitHub Actions)

This progression matches the skills commonly expected for 
entry-level to mid-level cloud and DevOps roles in the industry.


This roadmap is **very close to what companies actually use** for Cloud Engineer, DevOps Engineer, AWS Administrator, and SRE roles. If you learn these topics with **Linux + Bash + AWS CLI + hands-on projects**, you'll be well prepared for interviews.

